rComments: Exceptional Professor! Engaging Lectures, especially with Chemistry Connections slides. Always available for help including alternate office hours and weekend emails. Very fair assessments.
She's the best, always willing to help you out.

Dr Morra is definitely the best prof in the whole campus. She explains things very clearly, and she wants every student to succeed in this course. She cares about students' feeling and understands that some students may find the content hard, so she gives plenty of support including a lot of in class practice problems. Best prof ever!

I admire Dr Morra so much. She is funny, brilliant, and kind. Her tests are incredibly fair and she always encourages students to come by office hours or set up appointments if they need extra help. Easily one of my favourite profs, so glad I took this course and I hope I will run into her in the future :)

I think she's an angel, literally too perfect of a person. Dr. Morra is by far one of the most thorough and detailed professors I have ever had and is SO caring. She wants her students to do well and provides the best resources for them to do so. Every prof should reflect her teaching style and simply her character as a human being. She is a gem.

Beautiful inside and out. Makes lecture material clear, makes certain you understand concepts, and if you don't then she is available to answer your specific questions after class/at appts. I haven't yet finished her course and am taking it in the summer, but if my opinion changes I will update this rating.   Doubt it will, though! She's a gem.
teacherRatingTags: ['Caring', 'Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: The nicest, most beautiful and passionate professor I have ever had. The best.
Morra is amazingly helpful and her tests are set up to help you succeed. She's very good at explaining concepts and is clearly very passionate.

Dr. Morra is arguably the best lecturer that can teach and explain organic chemistry properly to her students. She's the most caring professor at the department and it really shows how she wants her students to succeed. She is easily approachable and will always have time to help you before each midterm and the final exam. Amazing person overall!

Best professor ever. She makes sure all students understand every concept before she goes on with different topics, and she continuously connects lecture material with relevant real-world applications. She teaches with great enthusiasm and she makes me look forward to attending class every week.

She is passionate about teaching and explains concepts clearly. She cares for her students and goes over examples to enforce concepts. She made the course fun and interesting. She didnt make the tests but overall the course is fair if you study effectively and practice off past tests. A caring professor that teaches well. I recomend taking with her

Dr. Morra is so lovely! So happy she taught me orgo. She explains concepts clearly and genuinely wants her students to do well - I say this because she responds to emails promptly/makes herself available to help out students..and she gives hints on what's going to be tested. Her lecturing style makes orgo easy to learn and interesting too.

She's a really great lecturer. Made difficult concepts easier to understand, especially all the reagents. I got really distracted by the fact that she's really pretty for a chem professor too >_<. Do previous tests instead of textbook questions since text questions are not good prep for the tests. A great prof overall but a challenging course.
Excellent prof. Very clear in teaching concepts and very clear in what she wanted you to know for the test. Fair tests, great prof, always available to help.
Very helpful lab coordinator. Patient, caring, straight forward. Has a nice friendly smile. :) A babe.
She was a great lab coordinator. Always came around to see how everyone was progressing. Very friendly
